<br>
Native Language - A Quest NPC should speak their native language and everyone else should suffer not understanding them.  This will seem quite odd when you're a gnome and only understand Ognit, but Al`Kabor is completely un-decipherable<br>
<br>
Local Language - If a Quest NPC is in a city, they should speak that language out of respect for the local populace, regardless of the NPC's native language.<br>
<br>
All Languages Present - A Quest NPC should retranslate everything they have said no matter how long it takes.  Of course, this would take a very long time and you still wouldn't understand everything going on in a multiple-person conversation.<br>
