ms that ran the recent quests had that ability, don't you think they would have done so instead of having people repeat themselves over and over again asking for understanding? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/23/01 5:49:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Quest Languages</span><hr size=1> It is possible for a GM character to speak (and listen to) any language such that you can understand, and be understood by him, perfectly, regardless of your skill in that language.<br>
